Key.French: Pour feter la victoire, les Nueviens ont decide de changer le nom de la Capitale apres un vote organise dans un journal parmi le peuple. Ainsi, la ville anciennement connue sous le nom de Santa Reina devient connue sous le nom de Marilla.
Key.Original: To celebrate the victory, the Nuevian people decided to change the name of the Capital after a vote organized in a newspaper among the people. Thus, the city formerly known as Santa Reina becomes known as Marilla.
Key.English: To celebrate the victory, the Nuevian people decided to change the name of the Capital after a vote organized in a newspaper among the people. Thus, the city formerly known as Santa Reina becomes known as Marilla.

Key.French: En juin 1926, le gouvernement americain decide de remettre en place un gouvernement nuevien pour se retirer de l'ile, tout en reprenant l'accord initial de liberation de Nueva.
Key.Original: In June 1926 the American government decided to put a Nuevian government back in place to withdraw from the island, while taking back the original agreement to free Nueva.
Key.English: In June 1926 the American government decided to put a Nuevian government back in place to withdraw from the island, while taking back the original agreement to free Nueva.

Key.French: Jusqu'en 1933, date de la levee de la Prohibition, jusqu'à 300 000 caisses d'alcool traversaient l'archipel chaque annee.
Key.Original: Until 1933, when Prohibition was lifted, up to 300,000 cases of alcohol passed through the archipelago each year.
Key.English: Until 1933, when Prohibition was lifted, up to 300,000 cases of alcohol passed through the archipelago each year.

Key.French: Depuis 1951, Notingo Agapito est le president general de la Republique unie de Nuevian.
Key.Original: Since 1951, Notingo Agapito has been the President-General of the United Nuevian Republic.
Key.English: Since 1951, Notingo Agapito has been the President-General of the United Nuevian Republic.
